Cell["\<\
We can easily see that the second dimension of the first core contracts with \
the first dimension of the second core and the third dimension of this latter \
contracts with the first dimension of the last core, giving rise to the 2x2x2 \
dimensions of the original tensor. Those are the auxiliary \[Alpha] indices, \
while the remnants are the i indices.\
\>", "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.991808963275858*^9, 3.991809004686207*^9}, {
  3.991809064228726*^9, 
  3.991809105149786*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"d47885b4-57f6-46d4-92ce-\
b417d34b98f1"]
}, Open  ]]
}, Open  ]],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["TT-QC Algorithm", "Section",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.991807998152507*^9, 
  3.9918080015366592`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"2d7936f8-db9a-4aba-b87d-\
046bc1d7ec85"],

Cell["\<\
In order to get the unitary operators used in the quantum circuit, we start \
from the TT decomposition obtained with the TT-SVD algorithm and recursively \
apply an unfolding and then an SVD to each TT-core.\
\>", "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.991808429873849*^9, 3.991808478629689*^9}, {
  3.991808623785783*^9, 
  3.9918086425754213`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"f7471fe8-7a85-44fa-909a-\
6e8399f39379"],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["First TT - core", "Subsection",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.9918092575745707`*^9, 
  3.991809263088628*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"cc0c7f9b-ebfd-4afb-999a-\
6872a006a60c"],

Cell["\<\
First we need to reshape the TT-core. To do so, we first get the dimensions \
of the first core:\
\>", "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.99180926942031*^9, 3.991809280778398*^9}, {
  3.9918095083831167`*^9, 3.991809552020668*^9}, {3.991809890203553*^9, 
  3.991809899822094*^9}, {3.99187712096905*^9, 3.99187712192402*^9}, {
  3.991877459948695*^9, 3.9918774783681498`*^9}, {3.991887575186289*^9, 
  3.991887584328559*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"3eaf2db9-cf18-4992-b994-\
a6f9a8c00f9f"],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell[BoxData[{
 RowBox[{
  RowBox[{"dims1", "=", 
   RowBox[{"Dimensions", "[", "Core1", "]"}]}], 
  ";"}], "\[IndentingNewLine]", "dims1"}], "Input",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.9918770010963373`*^9, 3.991877106969665*^9}, {
  3.991877137222732*^9, 3.991877167694519*^9}, {3.99187743449275*^9, 
